    "feat": {
        "name": "Oracular Warning",
        "type": "stat_block_section",
        "subtype": "feat",
        "text": "You have a premonition about impending danger that you use to warn your allies. Each ally within 20 feet gains a +2 status bonus to their initiative roll and gains temporary Hit Points equal to half your level, which last for 1 minute. If you are cursebound 2 when you use Oracular Warning, the bonus increases to +3, and if you are cursebound 3, the bonus increases to +4.",
        "level": 1,
        "action_type": {
            "type": "stat_block_section",
            "subtype": "action_type",
            "name": "Free Action"
        },
        "traits": [
            {
                "name": "Auditory",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 16,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 453",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 453",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        },
                        "page": 453,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "84c09922ddd30f2144494f2cb6f19412",
                "text": "Auditory actions and effects rely on sound. An action with the auditory trait can be successfully performed only if the creature using the action can speak or otherwise produce the required sounds. A spell or effect with the auditory trait has its effect only if the target can hear it. This applies only to sound-based parts of the effect, as determined by the GM. This is different from a sonic effect, which still affects targets who can\u2019t hear it (such as deaf targets) as long as the effect itself makes sound."
            },
            {
                "name": "Cursebound",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 320,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core 2",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core 2 pg. 133",
                            "alt": "Player Core 2 pg. 133",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 227
                        },
                        "page": 133,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "1.1",
                            "alt": "1.1",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 227
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "eaa83a0ce77df3ca04bc61b30931d48c",
                "text": "Abilities with this trait tighten your oracular curse's grasp on your soul in exchange for divine insights, giving you the cursebound condition. When you use a cursebound ability, you become cursebound 1, or if you were already cursebound, you increase the value of your cursebound condition by 1. As cursebound abilities are directly linked to your oracular curse, you can't use a cursebound ability if you don't have an oracular curse or if you are already at your maximum cursebound value. You can't mitigate or bypass the drawbacks of any cursebound ability with spells or other effects, and the effects of any cursebound ability end when you Refocus and remove the cursebound condition. A cursebound ability that allows a defense uses your spell attack modifier or spell DC unless noted otherwise.",
                "links": [
                    {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "oracular",
                        "alt": "oracular",
                        "game-obj": "Classes",
                        "aonid": 61
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Refocus",
                        "alt": "Refocus",
                        "game-obj": "Actions",
                        "aonid": 2621
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Divine",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 48,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 455",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 455",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        },
                        "page": 455,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "243cd4d729d5eddd1e2c4635b7985fb9",
                "text": "This magic comes from the divine tradition, drawing power from deities or similar sources. Anything with this trait is magical.  \n  \nA creature with this trait is primarily constituted of or has a strong connection to divine magic."
            },
            {
                "name": "Emotion",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 60,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 455",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 455",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        },
                        "page": 455,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "fb5f8b3d849b073e1514a6a025810470",
                "text": "This effect alters a creature\u2019s emotions. Effects with this trait always have the mental trait as well. Creatures with special training or that have mechanical or artificial intelligence are immune to emotion effects."
            },
            {
                "name": "Mental",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 106,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
